    "title": "Merlyn Evans, Artist-in-Residence",
    "is_featured": false,
    "description": "In this solo exhibition, Merlyn Evans showed work that was largely created between 1956-1966. She was an artist-in-residence at the School of the Art Institute in Chicago, as per their exchange program with the Royal College of Art in London, England. Evans, who was an abstract painter during a time where such was discouraged, painted \u201cpersons, personhoods, or personas,\u201d as she wrote in the catalog for the exhibition. In doing so, she sought a visual and sensational equilibrium filtered through social commentary..",
